problem_data.title: Reconstruct Original Digits from English
problem_data.description: Given a string s containing an out-of-order English representation of digits 0-9, return the digits in ascending order.
problem_data.solution:
class Solution:
    def originalDigits(self, s):
        from collections import Counter
        count = Counter(s)
        out = {}
        
        out['0'] = count['z']
        out['2'] = count['w']
        out['4'] = count['u']
        out['6'] = count['x']
        out['8'] = count['g']
        
        out['3'] = count['h'] - out['8']
        out['5'] = count['f'] - out['4']
        out['7'] = count['s'] - out['6']
        
        out['1'] = count['o'] - out['0'] - out['2'] - out['4']
        out['9'] = count['i'] - out['5'] - out['6'] - out['8']
        
        res = [k * out[k] for k in sorted(out.keys())]
        return ''.join(res)
